<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Venture Global</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Love <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/33603614.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9lbmV=
yZ3ktb2lsL3RoZS11LXMtZ2FzLXN0YXJ0dXAtYXQtdGhlLWNlbnRlci1vZi1hbi1lcGljLWZldW=
Qtd2l0aC1nbG9iYWwtZW5lcmd5LWdpYW50cy1hNTlhMWIzOT9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3M2/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB01cb2a26" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">these guys</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Michael Sabel=C2=A0and his partner, both indus=
try novices, have made a fortune virtually overnight by building from scrat=
ch one of the world=E2=80=99s largest gas exporters. They have also made so=
me powerful enemies.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here at this sprawling facility spanning about=
 630 acres in the wetlands outside New Orleans, Sabel said his company,=C2=
=A0Venture Global LNG, is on pace to leapfrog competitors and to rival Qata=
r as one of the world=E2=80=99s top exporters of liquefied natural gas by 2=
030.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But he must navigate a nasty feud with some of=
 the industry=E2=80=99s biggest names.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Venture Global=E2=80=99s earliest customers, i=
ncluding the oil giants BP and Shell, say the upstart company is ripping th=
em off. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BP and Shell argue that under the long-term co=
ntracts they signed over the past decade with Venture Global, they should h=
ave begun receiving LNG cargoes months ago, which they could sell through t=
heir vast trading arms. Instead, when the Ukraine war broke out, and LNG pr=
ices soared, Venture Global sold its gas at higher prices on the spot marke=
t=E2=80=94raking in more than $14 billion in sales.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s very unusual, and it=E2=
=80=99s very disappointing,=E2=80=9D Shell CEO=C2=A0Wael Sawan=C2=A0said in=
 a November interview. =E2=80=9CThis is, of course, a project that was unde=
rpinned by the offtake agreements that companies like ours provided.=E2=80=
=9D<br /><br />Venture Global counters that the contracts require it to del=
iver LNG to those early customers only when its first plant in Louisiana, c=
alled Calcasieu Pass, is finished. And it says even though the plant has sh=
ipped more than 200 cargoes, it isn=E2=80=99t technically complete. Twenty-=
one months after Venture Global=E2=80=99s first overseas shipment, BP, Shel=
l and other early buyers are still waiting, and seething.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/33603614.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDgvZG9uLXQtZG8tZGVhbHMtb24tbGlua2VkaW4_Y21waWQ9QkJE=
MTIwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXI=
mdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB4cd6c8d8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;"> talked about this in August</a>, but now there is a =
Wall Street Journal profile of Venture Global and the dispute, and it =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0is really not more complicated than I thought it was? Venture G=
lobal has long-term supply contracts with customers like BP and Shell, requ=
iring it to sell them LNG cargoes at fixed prices. It signed these contract=
s well before it built its facility, =E2=80=9Cputting the project on the ma=
p and giving big banks confidence to provide financing=E2=80=9D to build it=
, as the Journal reports. The customers got discounted prices in exchange f=
or taking a risk on an unproven new venture; Venture Global got commitments=
 that allowed it to build its facility. The way those contracts work is tha=
t Venture Global has to start delivering gas to the buyers when work on its=
 plant is done and it enters commercial operation. I wrote in August:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It has a plant in Louisiana that =
=E2=80=9Chas yet to enter commercial operations,=E2=80=9D but that neverthe=
less produces and sells LNG. There is some philosophical distinction there =
that eludes me: Intuitively, if you have a factory that is producing and se=
lling LNG, that would seem to be a commercial operation, but apparently if =
there=E2=80=99s something wrong with your steam generators then, no, not co=
mmercial yet, fine.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then the spot price of natural gas shot up=
 and Venture Global started producing LNG and selling it in the spot market=
, arguing that, while the plant is complete enough to export LNG, it is not=
 <em>complete </em>complete, and so Venture Global doesn=E2=80=99t have to =
fulfill the contracts yet. =E2=80=9CDo not flip the metaphysical switch tha=
t turns your not-in-commercial-operation plant into an in-commercial-operat=
ion plant,=E2=80=9D I said. =E2=80=9CIn March, it told its long-term buyers=
 that serious malfunctions in the Calcasieu Pass power system would delay t=
heir contracted cargoes,=E2=80=9D says the Journal, though those malfunctio=
ns were not serious enough to delay the=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>cargoes, t=
he ones it is selling at much higher prices in the spot market. The long-te=
rm buyers do not like it. =E2=80=9CWhen the vast majority of your customers=
 are pursuing some form of litigation against you, it=E2=80=99s time to loo=
k in the mirror,=E2=80=9D the Shell spokesman said. Venture Global disagree=
s:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sabel said customers knew from the beginning t=
here would be an extended period to get the plant fully operational and the=
 company would sell cargoes to others during that period before fulfilling =
long-term contracts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CYou get all-time low prices, we get t=
o finish the facility,=E2=80=9D he said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I hope that eventually they get the facility <=
em>just about </em>finished, but they don=E2=80=99t, like, paint one last r=
ivet. And then they say =E2=80=9Coops, still not finished, see, unpainted r=
ivet,=E2=80=9D and keep selling LNG at high prices to spot buyers. (I hope =
Shell and BP grumble and buy at spot prices too!) And then eventually when =
gas prices drop and it=E2=80=99s less uneconomical for Venture Global to se=
ll at the contract prices, they say =E2=80=9Cokay fine fine=E2=80=9D and pa=
int the rivet. What a great trade.=C2=A0</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">AI signals</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two ways to use a computer to generate trading=
 signals would be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Think about subtle characteristics of=
 a company that might be good or bad for that company. Develop a hypothesis=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cexecutives who say =E2=80=98I=E2=80=99 on earnings=
 calls are bad narcissists, but executives who say =E2=80=98we=E2=80=99 on =
earnings calls are good inclusive leaders=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0and then =
use a computer to crunch the data and evaluate the hypothesis. Take the hyp=
otheses that are good =E2=80=94=C2=A0the signals that turn out to work =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and program them into a trading model, which uses the signals t=
o buy and sell stocks.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Just ask a =
computer =E2=80=9Cis this company good or what,=E2=80=9D and if the compute=
r says =E2=80=9Cyeah it=E2=80=99s good=E2=80=9D you buy the stock.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The advantage of the first method is that it i=
s comprehensible; you can, at some level, explain your strategy, because yo=
u have reasons for every signal. Also those signals are more likely to be r=
obust, less likely to be just statistical artifacts, if there is some expli=
cable reasoning behind them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The advantage of the second method is, what if=
 the computer is smarter than you? What if it sees subtle patterns that you=
 miss?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33603614.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTItMDYvd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtcXVhbnRzLWpvaW4tY=
2hhdGJvdC1ib29tLWFzLWFpLWdvbGQtcnVzaC1pbnRlbnNpZmllcz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjA2MjNf=
TU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGV=
ybT0yMzEyMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB023e0=
5c6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Justina Lee</a> on =E2=80=9Cwhat artific=
ial-intelligence proponents are dreaming up these days, thanks to the compu=
tational firepower of language models like ChatGPT=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At its core, linguistic data-crunching seeks t=
o help quants get better at predicting the future by analyzing the meaning =
of the text behind the numbers.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over at AllianceBernstein, data scientists And=
rew Chin and Yuyu Fan are going all-in on AI tools to find hidden meanings =
in corporate spiel. Not every attempt has worked. For instance, when they d=
ug into how Chinese companies summarize on-site visits from brokers, they f=
ound that the more complex the text =E2=80=94 like the length of sentences =
and unnecessary words =E2=80=94 the more evidence that the firm in question=
 is struggling.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, the number of words divided=
 by the length of the broker event, a proxy for speaking speed, didn=E2=80=
=99t mean much. In US earnings calls, they studied the use of the =E2=80=9C=
we=E2=80=9D pronoun as a sign of collaboration and unity. That also proved =
meaningless.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe really try to generate a broad set=
 of signals =E2=80=94 sometimes hundreds =E2=80=94 but it doesn=E2=80=99t m=
ean all of them will work,=E2=80=9D said Fan, a senior data scientist at th=
e $669 billion manager.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whereas machine reading used to rely on counti=
ng positive and negative words, the large language models behind chatbots a=
re far better at parsing context even across meandering paragraphs. These r=
obots not only purport to structure the unstructured, they also promise to =
automate research tasks and generate fresh trading ideas at breakneck speed=
. And the introduction of ChatGPT alone =E2=80=94 which has ingested enough=
 text that it has a good grasp of all subjects =E2=80=94 is a regime shift.=
 Academic researchers have found that simply telling the chatbot to rate if=
 a news headline is good or bad for a stock has produced better results tha=
n prior methods.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can construct a query like =E2=80=9Cdoes t=
his news story indicate that the company=E2=80=99s leadership team is colla=
borative and not using complex answers to hide the truth,=E2=80=9D or you c=
an construct a query like =E2=80=9Ccomputer, would you buy this stock?=E2=
=80=9D I guess you=E2=80=99d feel better about your own contributions if yo=
u asked the more complicated questions. Like, you are in charge here and th=
e computer is just helping with the analysis. But =E2=80=9Csimply telling t=
he chatbot to rate if a news headline is good or bad for a stock has produc=
ed better results than prior methods.=E2=80=9D</p>
